Now, the second part of the problem: the second Java program takes an integer n and outputs the sequence of numbers starting from n, then the largest possible divisor less than the previous, etc. The second Java program's code:

public class codeforces_58_B {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws java.lang. Exception {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        System.out.println(n + " ");
        int m = n;
        for (int i = n - 1; i > 0; i--) { if (m % i == 0) {
                System.out.println(i + " ");
                m = i;
            }
        }
    }
} Wait, the code is using System.out.println for each number, with a space. So the output is like "6 5 4 3 2 1 " but with each number followed by a space and a new line? Or is it all on one line? Looking at the code:

The first line is System.out.println(n + " "); which adds a space and a new line. Then, for each i from n-1 down to 1, if m%i ==0, it does System.out.println(i + " "); again adding a space and new line. So the output is each number on its own line with a trailing space. But the problem says that the second program's output is the input to the next, but in this case, the second program is the last, so its output is the final output of the entire Fortran program.

